Russian International Reserves Decline to $532 Billion in Week

-- B y   T o r r e y   C l a r k
-- 
2011-09-22T05:52:30Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-09-22/russian-international-reserves-decline-to-532-billion-in-week.html
Russia’s international gold and
currency reserves fell $6.8 billion to $532 billion in the week
to Sept. 16, the central bank said.  That is the biggest decline in three months, according to
Bank Rossii’s website.  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Torrey Clark at 
